org.opendaylight.yang.gen.v1.urn.ietf.params.xml.ns.yang.ietf.netconf.monitoring.rev101004.netconf.state

Interface Statistics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.Augmentable<Statistics>, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.ChildOf<NetconfState>, CommonCounters, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.DataContainer, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.DataObject

    public interface Statistics
extends org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.ChildOf<NetconfState>, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.Augmentable<Statistics>, CommonCounters
    Statistical data pertaining to the NETCONF server.

    This class represents the following YANG schema fragment defined in module ietf-netconf-monitoring
    (Source path: META-INF/yang/ietf-netconf-monitoring.yang): 

     container statistics {
     leaf netconf-start-time {
         type date-and-time;
     }
     leaf in-bad-hellos {
         type zero-based-counter32;
     }
     leaf in-sessions {
         type zero-based-counter32;
     }
     leaf dropped-sessions {
         type zero-based-counter32;
     }
     leaf in-rpcs {
         type zero-based-counter32;
     }
     leaf in-bad-rpcs {
         type zero-based-counter32;
     }
     leaf out-rpc-errors {
         type zero-based-counter32;
     }
     leaf out-notifications {
         type zero-based-counter32;
     }
     uses common-counters;
 }
    The schema path to identify an instance is ietf-netconf-monitoring/netconf-state/statistics

    To create instances of this class use StatisticsBuilder.

    See Also:
    StatisticsBuilder

      • getInBadHellos

        org.opendaylight.yang.gen.v1.urn.ietf.params.xml.ns.yang.ietf.yang.types.rev100924.ZeroBasedCounter32 getInBadHellos()
        Number of sessions silently dropped because an invalid message was received. This includes messages with a 'session-id' attribute, bad namespace, and bad capability declarations.

      • getInSessions

        org.opendaylight.yang.gen.v1.urn.ietf.params.xml.ns.yang.ietf.yang.types.rev100924.ZeroBasedCounter32 getInSessions()
        Number of sessions started. This counter is incremented when a message with a is sent. 'in-sessions' - 'in-bad-hellos' = 'number of correctly started netconf sessions'

      • getDroppedSessions

        org.opendaylight.yang.gen.v1.urn.ietf.params.xml.ns.yang.ietf.yang.types.rev100924.ZeroBasedCounter32 getDroppedSessions()
        Number of sessions that were abnormally terminated, e.g., due to idle timeout or transport close. This counter is not incremented when a session is properly closed by a operation, or killed by a operation.
